From: Pascal Ledesma <pascal@ingeniousdigital.com>
Date: 2026-05-02
Subject: [PATCH] wifi_manager: disable modem-sleep after STA association

With Wi-Fi modem-sleep enabled (the IDF default WIFI_PS_MIN_MODEM),
outbound TCP packets get delayed by 100-300 ms while the modem
naps between beacons. For tiny responses (/api/status ~ 200 B) the
delay is invisible, but for the camera snapshot endpoint a 50 KB
JPEG is fragmented into many segments and curl times out before
all of them arrive — http=200 with 0 bytes received in 60s, on a
loop. Browsers see the same hang.

The fix is one line: call esp_wifi_set_ps(WIFI_PS_NONE) after the
STA association completes. We pay ~30 mA more idle current in
exchange for reliable HTTP throughput across all response sizes.

Note: setting PS at esp_wifi_start time does not stick — the
fresh association resets PS back to the default. Has to run from
the IP_EVENT_STA_GOT_IP handler.

Patch target:
  components/common/wifi_manager/wifi_manager.c

---
diff --git a/components/common/wifi_manager/wifi_manager.c b/components/common/wifi_manager/wifi_manager.c
--- a/components/common/wifi_manager/wifi_manager.c
+++ b/components/common/wifi_manager/wifi_manager.c
@@ -261,6 +261,13 @@ static void wifi_event_handler(void *arg,
         s_retry_count = 0;
         s_connected = true;
         s_mode = s_ap_active ? WIFI_MODE_APSTA_OK : s_mode;
+        // Disable Wi-Fi modem-sleep AFTER association — must run here
+        // (not at esp_wifi_start) because the new association resets
+        // PS to default MIN_MODEM, which delays outbound TCP packets
+        // by hundreds of ms and makes /api/camera/snapshot (~50 KB
+        // JPEG) un-deliverable to a browser client. Trades ~30 mA
+        // idle current for reliable HTTP throughput.
+        (void)esp_wifi_set_ps(WIFI_PS_NONE);
         xEventGroupSetBits(s_wifi_event_group, WIFI_CONNECTED_BIT);
         notify_state_changed(true);
     }
